<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98847859958576></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98847859958576><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98847859958576>RE: Paladin of Sorrow</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=98847859958576#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Apr 28th 1:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just buy the freaking armor, there is too much going on in this game to be worried about acquiring your class specific Armor.&nbsp;&nbsp;You want it easy, go to Eastern Waste, get in a group that camps the Rygor Orc keep and loot as many Rygor armor as you can.  Rygor is worth and comparable to Ro.  There are so many armors out there that are equal or even better than the Ro armor which almost any class or race can wear.  <br>I tried all that Ro quest before and it bites, so I didnt finish it. I finaly just bought the damn things, what? buying isnt a crime.  At least Verant is good enuff to make our armors sellable.  Adapt and Improvise brother paladin.  Thinking instead of whining can help you out sometimes.<br><br>Level 41 paladin<br>Cazic thule<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
