	   <tr><td colspan=2>I feel your pain, and have lived through it on several occassions.&nbsp;&nbsp;True the Ro armor quests are VERY time consuming and difficult, I've only completed a couple myself (and you DO NOT need to be a master smith to make Ro Armor - you could do it succesfully with a skill lvl of 1 in smithing). I on the other hand am a master smith, I feel as a dwarve it is in my heritage to strive and make my own stuff.  <br><br>I understand about the Shield quest as well, I had the same problem with my quest for the Aegis of Life.  After 48 hours of on agian, off again camping with no spawn, I decided to put it on the backburner and try later (I still want one btw).<br><br>I agree that Paladins are the "whipping boys" of verant.  It frustrating to be out-tanked by a mage's pet.  But, I never have a problem getting into a group due to the fact that I have special abilities other than being a "meat-shield".  Unlike a warrior, I can stun and bash the moster to death.  I can heal on par with a druid (minus chloroplast), I can buff a step below a cleric. And when all else fails and the party looks like it's about to be wiped out- LoH. I've tried other tanking classes, I have a warrior alt about lvl 30 now, and I find myself in the character selection screen picking my favorite of the 3 I play- a Paladin!  Call me a mascochist, but I love playing one and will continue to play my pali till one of 1 thing happens:  I get tired of EQ and quit playing.  It's not going to happen in the near future as I like the ppl I know and grew up with (in EQ) and EQ is still as fun as the day I opened the box and put it on my computer.<br>&nbsp;<br>Dadin <br>54th Cavalier<br>Honored Circle on Xev<br><br>Dwarven Thane<br>Hellwinds - Palomides </td></tr>
